Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_library_set(25.10)                                  get_library_set(25.10)

Name
       get_library_set - Returns a Tcl list of the timing or cdB libraries for
       the specified library set

Syntax
        get_library_set

       <libSetName>{-timing  | -si | -aocv | -socv}

       Returns a Tcl list of the timing or cdB libraries for the specified li-
       brary set.

       Use  this  command  after creating at least one library set (create_li-
       brary_set).

Parameters
       -aocv  Returns AOCV library names for the specified library set.

       <libSetName>
              Specifies the name of the library set.

       -si <libSetName>
              Returns the cdb library names for the specified library set.

       -socv  Returns the SOCV library names for the specified library set.

       -timing
              Returns a list of the timing libraries for the specified library
              set.

              This list contains the names of files from where  the  libraries
              were sourced from.

Examples
              * The following commands create the library sets IsCOM-1V:

                create_library_set   -name   IsCOM-1V   -timing   [list   std-
                cell_F_1V.lib ram_F.lib pad.lib]

                  -si [list stdcell_F_2.cdb ram_F.cdb pad.cdb}]

              * The following command returns a TCL list  of  the  timing  li-
                braries for library set IsCOM-1V:

                get_library_set -timing IsCOM-1V

                The software returns the following results:

                {stdcell_F_1V.lib ram_F.lib pad.lib}

Related Information
